{"title_page": "Nen\u00e9 (footballer, born 1979)", "text_new": "{{Infobox football biography\n| name = Nen\u00e9\n| image =\n| fullname = Adriano Barbosa Miranda da Luz\n| birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1979|8|24|df=y}}\n| birth_place = [[Lisbon]], [[Portugal]]\n| height = {{convert|1.86|m|ftin|0|abbr=on}}\n| position = [[Midfielder#Central midfielder|Midfielder]]\n| currentclub =\n| clubnumber =\n| youthyears1 = 1989\u20131991 | youthclubs1 = \u00c1guias da P\u00f3voa\n| youthyears2 = 1991\u20131994 | youthclubs2 = Ponte Frielas\n| youthyears3 = 1994\u20131997 | youthclubs3 = [[Odivelas F.C.|Odivelas]]\n| youthyears4 = 1997\u20131998 | youthclubs4 = [[Boavista F.C.|Boavista]]\n| years1 = 1998\u20131999 | clubs1 = [[F.C. Marco|Marco]] | caps1 = 25 | goals1 = 2\n| years2 = 1999\u20132000 | clubs2 = [[U.D. Vilafranquense|Vilafranquense]] | caps2 = 35 | goals2 = 2\n| years3 = 2000\u20132002 | clubs3 = [[Gondomar S.C.|Gondomar]] | caps3 = 45 | goals3 = 5\n| years4 = 2002 | clubs4 = [[S.C. Braga B|Braga B]] | caps4 = 11 | goals4 = 2\n| years5 = 2002\u20132005 | clubs5 = [[S.C. Braga|Braga]] | caps5 = 38 | goals5 = 0\n| years6 = 2004 | clubs6 = \u2192 [[\u00c7aykur Rizespor]] (loan) | caps6 = 5 | goals6 = 0\n| years7 = 2004\u20132005 | clubs7 = \u2192 [[C.D. Aves|Aves]] (loan) | caps7 = 31 | goals7 = 3 \n| years8 = 2005\u20132006 | clubs8 = [[U.D. Leiria|Uni\u00e3o Leiria]] | caps8 = 5 | goals8 = 0\n| years9 = 2006 | clubs9 = \u2192 [[C.D. Aves|Aves]] (loan) | caps9 = 13 | goals9 = 3\n| years10 = 2006\u20132007 | clubs10 = [[C.D. Aves|Aves]] | caps10 = 18 | goals10 = 1\n| years11 = 2007 | clubs11 = [[Al-Arabi SC (Kuwait)|Al Arabi]] | caps11 = | goals11 =\n| years12 = 2008 | clubs12 = [[Enosis Neon Paralimni FC|Enosis Neon]] | caps12 = 12 | goals12 = 0\n| years13 = 2009 | clubs13 = [[Pontevedra CF|Pontevedra]] | caps13 = 18 | goals13 = 0\n| years14 = 2009\u20132010 | clubs14 = [[FC Bra\u015fov|Bra\u015fov]] | caps14 = 9 | goals14 = 0\n| years15 = 2010\u20132012 | clubs15 = [[F.C. Arouca|Arouca]] | caps15 = 49 | goals15 = 0\n| years16 = 2012\u20132013 | clubs16 = [[S.C. Covilh\u00e3|Covilh\u00e3]] | caps16 = 47 | goals16 = 1\n| years17 = 2014 | clubs17 = [[F.C. Famalic\u00e3o|Famalic\u00e3o]] | caps17 = 14 | goals17 = 2\n| years18 = 2014\u20132019 | clubs18 = [[Vilaverdense F.C.|Vilaverdense]] | caps18 = 159 | goals18 = 20<!-- LEAGUE GAMES ONLY -->\n| totalcaps = | totalgoals =\n| nationalyears1 = 2004\u20132008 | nationalteam1 = [[Cape Verde national football team|Cape Verde]] | nationalcaps1 = 14 | nationalgoals1 = 0\n| club-update = 5 May 2019\n| nationalteam-update =\n}}\n\n'''Adriano Barbosa Miranda da Luz''' (born 24 August 1979), commonly known as '''Nen\u00e9''', is a [[Cape Verde]]an professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Midfielder#Central midfielder|central midfielder]].\n\n==Club career==\nBorn in the capital [[Lisbon]], Nen\u00e9 spent most of his professional career in Portugal. After starting out in the lower leagues, he signed in early 2002 with [[Primeira Liga]] club [[S.C. Braga]] from [[Gondomar S.C.|Gondomar SC]], 31 of his 38 league games with the [[Minho Province|Minho]] team coming in the [[2002\u201303 Primeira Liga|2002\u201303 season]], in a 14th-place finish.\n\nAfter definitively leaving Braga (which also loaned him twice during his spell), Nen\u00e9 signed with [[U.D. Leiria]] which in turn loaned him to [[C.D. Aves]], with the latter side promoting to the top division at the end of [[2005\u201306 Liga de Honra|2005\u201306]]. The move was subsequently made permanent, and the player was relatively used [[2006\u201307 Primeira Liga|the following campaign]] \u2013 1,131 minutes, one goal in a 1\u20132 away loss against [[Boavista F.C.|Boavista FC]],<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.record.pt/futebol/futebol-nacional/liga-nos/aves/detalhe/boavista-aves-2-1-ricardo-silva-74-linz-902-nene-9.html|title=Boavista-Aves, 2\u20131 (Ricardo Silva 74, Linz 90+2; Nen\u00e9 9)|newspaper=[[Record (newspaper)|Record]]|language=pt|date=4 November 2006|accessdate=13 December 2017}}</ref> whom he had represented as a youth \u2013 which ended in immediate relegation.\n\nNen\u00e9 rarely settled in the following years, playing in [[Kuwait]], [[Cyprus]], Spain and [[Romania]]. In [[2010\u201311 Liga de Honra|2010\u201311]], aged 31, he returned to his birth nation and joined [[F.C. Arouca]], promoted for the first time ever to the [[Segunda Liga|second tier]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://desporto.sapo.pt/futebol/segunda-liga/artigos/nene-chegou-a-acordo-por-uma-epoca|title=Nen\u00e9 chegou a acordo por uma \u00e9poca|trans-title=Nen\u00e9 agreed to one season|publisher=[[SAPO (company)|SAPO]]|language=pt|date=12 July 2012|accessdate=4 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n==International career==\nNen\u00e9 was part of the [[Cape Verde national football team|Cape Verde]] squad which progressed to the second stage of the [[2006 FIFA World Cup]] [[2006 FIFA World Cup qualification (CAF)|qualifiers]], appearing in six out of 12 possible matches. The national team finished second bottom in their group, failing to qualify for both the competition in [[Germany]] and the [[2006 Africa Cup of Nations]].<ref>{{FIFA|214788}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{ForaDeJogo|197908240001}}\n*{{BDFutbol|100202}}\n*{{NFT|7707}}\n*{{Soccerway|adriano-barbosa-miranda/71226}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Nene}}\n[[Category:1979 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Portuguese people of Cape Verdean descent]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Lisbon]]\n[[Category:Cape Verdean footballers]]\n[[Category:Portuguese footballers]]\n[[Category:Association football midfielders]]\n[[Category:Primeira Liga players]]\n[[Category:LigaPro players]]\n[[Category:Portuguese Second Division players]]\n[[Category:F.C. Marco players]]\n[[Category:Gondomar S.C. players]]\n[[Category:S.C. Braga B players]]\n[[Category:S.C. Braga players]]\n[[Category:C.D. Aves players]]\n[[Category:U.D. Leiria p