6 Philippine presidential election]]\n[[Category:Members of the House of Representatives of the Philippines from Camarines Sur]]\n[[Category:People from Naga, Camarines Sur]]\n[[Category:University of the Philippines Diliman alumni]]\n[[Category:San Beda University alumni]]\n[[Category:Chairpersons of the Housing and Urban Development Coordinating Council of the Philippines]]\n[[Category:Duterte Administration cabinet members]]\n[[Category:Filipino radio personalities]]\n[[Category:21st-century women politicians]]\n[[Category:Women members of the House of Representatives of the Philippines]]\n[[Category:Women members of the Cabinet of the Philippines]]\n[[Category:Women vice presidents]]\n", "name_user": "152.32.111.92", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "(Updated some major information on the article.)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Leni_Robredo"}
{"title_page": "Khaled Ramadan", "text_new": "{{COI|date=September 2018}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2016}}\n\n'''Khaled Ramadan''' (born in 1973) consultant, [[curator]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://maldivespavilion.com/blog/about/|title=About - Maldives Pavilion - 55th Venice Biennale|website=Maldivespavilion.com|accessdate=4 November 2018}}</ref> filmmaker<ref>{{cite web|url=https://vimeo.com/86557708|title=Eye in Hand - E\u015fref Arma\u011fan|website=Vimeo.com|accessdate=4 November 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://vimeo.com/43397737|title=I Told President Mubarak|website=Vimeo.com|accessdate=4 November 2018}}</ref> educator,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.akbild.ac.at/Portal/institute/bildende-kunst/vortrage-events/the-panache-of-artivism-within-the-imperial-cultural-narrative-of-the-middle-east?set_language=de&cl=de&backurl=https://www.akbild.ac.at/resolveuid/44746f5dc4c153575dde87ffed987e0b?b_start=5|title=The Panache of Artivism within the Imperial Cultural Narrative of the Middle East|website=Akbild.ac.at|accessdate=4 November 2018}}</ref> and cultural writer.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.khaledramadan.org/|title=Khaled Ramadan - Don Juan Report|website=Khaledramadan.org|accessdate=4 November 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.artforum.com/diary/id=29765|title=Playing with Fire|website=Artforum.com|accessdate=4 November 2018}}</ref>\nCurrently, he is working as an examiner for the higher artistic educational programmes under The Danish Ministry of Higher Education and Science and as an evaluator of Alto University professorship program. He is the co-editor of the new book, Journalism in Times of War, by Al Jazeera Media Institute, (2018) Aljazeera TV Doha.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://studies.aljazeera.net/en/publications/archive/2016.html|title=2016|website=Studies.aljazeera.net|accessdate=4 November 2018}}</ref> He is the new appointed director of the Media Art Research Space \u2013 MARC, Production and Exhibition Spaces of Art and Film - Antalya, open in April 2017. Previously, Ramadan has worked as director of BMAF, Muscat,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2016/04/27/arts/international/a-helping-hand-for-film-artists-in-oman.html?_r=0|title=A Helping Hand for Film Artists in Oman|website=Nytimes.com|accessdate=4 November 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.selectionsarts.com/2016/03/questions-of-practice/|title=Questions of Practice - Selections Arts|date=30 March 2016|website=Selectionsarts.com|accessdate=4 November 2018}}</ref> a senior advisor for the Maldives Ministry of Culture<ref name=\"maldivespavilion.com\">{{cite web|url=http://www.maldivespavilion.com|title=Maldives Pavilion|website=Maldivespavilion.com|accessdate=4 November 2018}}</ref> and for the Danish Arts Council,<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.kunst.dk/initiativer/kunst-globalisering/interkulturelt-raadgivningsprojekt/the-danish-arts-councils-intercultural-advisory-project/ |title=Archived copy |access-date=9 November 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161109154300/http://www.kunst.dk/initiativer/kunst-globalisering/interkulturelt-raadgivningsprojekt/the-danish-arts-councils-intercultural-advisory-project/ |archive-date=9 November 2016 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all }}</ref> and as an external consultant for the Prince Claus Fund,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.chamberarchive.org/blog/consultants/|title=Consultants - Chamber of Public Secrets|website=Chamberarchive.org|accessdate=4 November 2018}}</ref> the Manifesta Foundation,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://manifesta.org/manifesta-8/|title=Manifesta 8 \u00ab  MANIFESTA|website=Manifesta.org|accessdate=4 November 2018}}</ref> and the Nordic Institute for Contemporary Arts (NIFCA).\n\n==Projects==\nRamadan has curated and co-curated projects like Climate Maters, Ipoh International Art Festival, Malaysia 2019,<ref>https://www.thestar.com.my/lifestyle/culture/2019/11/26/ipoh-international-art-festival-celebrates-the-strength-of-city039s-creative-communities</ref>\u00a0The Third Guangzhou Triennial at the Guangdong Museum of Modern Art, China and UCCA, Beijing; Museo Nacional Centro de Arte Reina Sof\u00eda, Madrid,  KW Berlin, Germany and Outflow, Kumho Museum of Art in Seoul, South Korea. In 2013, he was the appointed curator for the [[Maldives Pavilion]] at the 55th<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.artsy.net/article/maldivespavilion-khaled-ramadans-documentary-maldives-to-be-or|title=Khaled Ramadan\u2019s Documentary: \"Maldives To Be or Not\"|date=25 May 2013|website=Artsy.net|accessdate=4 November 2018}}</ref> [[Venice Biennale]].<ref name=\"maldivespavilion.com\"/> In 2010, together with Chamber of Public Secrets, he was appointed co-curator of [[Manifesta]] 8 in Spain.{{citation needed|date=February 2018}}\n\nRamadan<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.chamberarchive.org|title=Chamber of Public Secrets|website=Chamberarchive.org|accessdate=4 November 2018}}</ref> and Alfredo Cramerotti<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ibraaz.org/platforms/6/responses/11/|title=Response to Platform 6 by CPS Chamber of Public Secrets|website=Ibraaz.org|accessdate=4 November 2018}}</ref> are the co-founder of the art collective Chamber of Public Secrets, which has existed since 2004. In 2006, Ramadan co-founded Doculogia, a platform for critical media.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.doculogia.com|title=DocuLogia|website=Doculogia.com|accessdate=4 November 2018}}</ref> In 2009, Al-Jazeera TV produced a documentary about Ramadan's activities and achievements.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.aljazeera.net/programs/a-date-in-exile/2009/3/29/%D8%AE%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%AF-%D8%B1%D9%85%D8%B6%D8%A7%D9%86 |title=Archived copy |access-date=22 November 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304062337/http://www.aljazeera.net/programs/a-date-in-exile/2009/3/29/%D8%AE%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%AF-%D8%B1%D9%85%D8%B6%D8%A7%D9%86 |archive-date=4 March 2016 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n\nRamadan is a member of the International Association of Art Critics (AICA), and the International Association of Curators of Contemporary Art (IKT) and [21]. He is a nominator of The Sovereign Asian Art Prize, The Jameel Prize, International Award for Contemporary Art and Design, the Prince Claus Fund Awards, and pecial correspondents and nominator for the Future Generation Art Prize, at the Victor Pinchuk Foundation in Kyiv, Ukraine. \n\n==Author==\nHe is the author of Peripheral Insider: Perspectives on Contemporary Internationalism in Visual Culture, published by Copenhagen University Press, 2007.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.co.uk/gp/search?index=books&linkCode=qs&keywords=9788772899671|title=Amazon.co.uk: 9788772899671: Books|website=Amazon.co.uk|accessdate=4 November 2018}}</ref>\nJournalism In Times of War, edited by Awad Joumaa and Khaled Ramadan.<ref>https://www.aljazeera.com/blogs/middleeast/2018/01/journalism-times-war-middle-east-perspective-180124070626008.html</ref>\n\nHe regularly contributes to international magazines<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ebiz.turpin-distribution.com/products/282888-transvisuality-the-cultural-dimension-of-visuality-olume2-visual-organisations.aspx|title=Turpin Distribution. TransVisuality: The Cultural Dimension of Visuality: Volume 2: Visual Organisations|website=Ebiz.turpin-distribution.com|accessdate=4 November 2018}}</ref> and journals<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20050520232043/http://www.mtp.hum.ku.dk/details.asp?ELN=200733]</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.com/Peripheral-Insider-Perspectives-Contemporary-Internationalism/dp/8772899670|title=Peripheral Insider: Perspectives on Contemporary Internationalism in Visual Culture|editor-first=Khaled D.|editor-last=Ramadan|date=12 April 2007|publisher=Museum Tusculanum Press|accessdate=4 November 2018}}</ref> on topics such as art,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.chamberarchive.org/blog/peripheral-insider/|title=Peripheral Insider - Chamber of Public Secrets|website=Chamberarchive.org|accessdate=4 November 2018}}</ref> media, aesthetics and social activism, latest e.g. in Border Thinking: Disassembling Histories of Racialized Violence, ed. Marina Gr\u017eini\u0107, Sternberg Press (2018). Set City, the Age of Reality Cinematography, is the title of Khaled Ramadan\u2019s contribution to the book.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sternberg-press.com/index.php?pageId=1820&l=en&bookId=714|title=Sternberg Press - Marina Gr\u017eini\u0107 (Ed.)|website=Sternberg-press.com|accessdate=4 November 2018}}</ref> Trans-Visuality, published by Liverpool University  Press.\n\n==Works==\nRecent work includes, The Panache of Artivism within the Imperial Narrative of the Middle East, published in 2017 in the book, Independent Republic of Culture - Edited by Serhan Ada, published by Cultural Policy and Management Research Centre, \u0130stanbul Bilgi \u00dcniversitesi Yay\u0131nlar\u0131/ Istanbul Bilgi University Press 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.schermodellarte.org/en/prize-2013/|title=Prize Lo schermo dell'arte Film Festival 2013|website=Schermodellarte.org|accessdate=4 November 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://hivevoices.org/2014/01/06/art-and-its-institutions-in-the-age-of-physical-absentia-by-khaled-ramadan/|title=Khaled Ramadan|date=6 January 2014|website=Hivevoices.org|accessdate=4 November 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.zerobooksonline.com/en/product/independent-republic-of-culture-cultural-policy-and-management-research-centre-kpy-yearbook_29_41056.html?r=22#sthash.9fvBJYwR.dpbs|title=Independent Republic Of Culture Cultural Policy And Management Research Centre (KPY) Yearbook|website=Zero Books Online|accessdate=4 November 2018}}</ref>\n\nRamadan\u2019s art-house filmmaking and theoretical writing has rewarded him a specialisation in cinematic visual analysis and aesthetic framing.\nHe assisted aestheticizing several productions at the Film City in Denmark and the TV station AlJazeera.\n\nHis best cinematic visual analysis contribution is the essay, Set City - Post-Snuff Film and the New Age of Reality Cinematography, in Border Thinking, ed. Prof. Marina Gr\u017eini\u0107, part of the publication series of the Academy of Fine Arts Vienna 2018.\n\n==Writings==\nRamadan\u2019s writing are published with: \nSlavoj Zizek, Irit Rogoff, Benjamin R. Barber, Bernadette Buckley, Horacio Gonz\u00e1lez, Boris Groys, W.J.T. Mitchell, Ken Neil, Lila Pastoriza, James A. Walker, Peter Weibel, Joseba Zulaika, Hamid Dabashi, Thomas McEvilley, Sarat Maharaj, Rasheed Araeen, Gavin Jantjes, Simon Sheikh, Maaretta Jaukkuri, Gao Shiming, Max Ryyn\u00e4nen, Zygmunt Bauman and Antonio Zaya.\n\n==Videography==\nThe Return of the Real, with artist Veronica Bape, Dale Norway 2019. Red Line, with artist Kari Steihaug, Norway 2019. RobOman. Arabian Gulf, 2018; Outsourcing Torture. AJ co-production.  2016; Floating Community. Cambodia 2016; Romiah Selfie. Lebanon, 2015; Caf\u00e9 Fishawy. Egypt, 2014; Maldives To Be or Not. Maldives 2013; The Shadow of San Anton. Spain, 2010. I Told President Mubarak. Egypt 2010.  Eyes in Hand, about blind artist Esraf Armagan. Spain 2010. Out of Gaza. Gaza strip, 2009. Quest for the Brotherhood. Egypt, 2008.\nArab Media Landscape. Dubai, UAE, 2007;  Mapping the South. Lebanon, 2006;  Comrade Alfredo Neri. Denmark-Sweden-Italy, 2005;  Wide Power. Lebanon, 2004.\n\n==Participation==\n*Climate Maters, Ipoh International Art Festival, Malaysia 2019<ref>http://portipoh.com.my/phone/screening-and-talk.html</ref>\n*\u201cFrom a Place of Darkness\u201d Contemporary Istanbul, curated by Gulsen Bal 2019 <ref>https://www.contemporaryistanbul.com</ref>\n*For the Love of Air Liquid. Curated by Alfredo Cramerotti and Khaled Ramadan, Opening exhibition - Media Art Research Center (MARC), Antalya, April 2018. http://www.chamberarchive.org/blog/for-the-love-of-air-liquid/\n*What is left? Frei_raum Q21 exhibition space, Vienna, Austria, 2016.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.q21.at/en/program/c/programmdetail/what-is-left-1/|title=Q21|website=MuseumsQuartier Wien|accessdate=4 November 2018}}</ref>\n*Be-diversity, MUSE di Trento, Italy 2015.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.muse.it/it/Esplora/mostre-temporanee/Archivio/Pagine/Be-diversity.aspx|title=Be-diversity|website=Muse.it|accessdate=4 November 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=vtCpzg2dHgA|title=Be-diversity: Platform: RTTR: Aboulkheir Breigheche|author=Stefano Cagol|date=22 August 2015|accessdate=4 November 2018|publisher=[[YouTube]]}}</ref>\n*A Room of His Own, The Artsonje Center Seoul 2014.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://koreajoongangdaily.joins.com/news/article/article.aspx?aid=2999452|title=Exhibit explores changing position of men|website=Korea JoongAng Daily|accessdate=4 November 2018}}</ref>\n*Overflow, The Politics of Water, Kumho Museum of Art, Seoul 2014.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://activate.zone/waterscapes-pohang-2015/|title=Waterscapes - Pohang 2015|website=Activate.zone|accessdate=4 November 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://english.visitkorea.or.kr/enu/ATR/SI_EN_3_1_1_1.jsp?cid=268094|title=Kumho Museum of Art (\uae08\ud638\ubbf8\uc220\uad00) - Official Korea Tourism Organization|website=english.visitkorea.or.kr|accessdate=4 November 2018}}</ref>\n*The Maldives Pavilion at the 55th Venice Biennale 2013.\n*Manifesta 8, Spain, 2010.\n*Guangzhou Triennial, Guangdong Museum of Modern Art, China 2008. UCCA, Beijing, China, 2008.\n*Museo Nacional Centro de Arte Reina Sof\u00eda, Madrid 2007. Video Brazil.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://site.videobrasil.org.br/en/acervo/artistas/artista/145413|title=Khaled D. Ramadan - Videobrasil|website=Site.videobrasil.org.br|accessdate=4 November 2018}}</ref> KW Berlin, Germany, 2006.\n* MUSE - Museo delle Scienze di Trento, Italy.\n* Kumho Museum of Art, Seoul, Korea.\n* Museet for Samtidskunst, Roskilde, Denmark.\n* Herbert F. Johnson Museum of Art, NYC. USA.\n* Queens Museum of Art, New York City, NY. USA.\n* Quartier \u00c9ph\u00e9m\u00e8re, Fonderie Darling, Montreal, Canada.\n* The Third Guangzhou Triennial Guangdong Museum of Art, Guangzhou, China.\n* Casino Luxembourg. Luxembourg.\n* Ars Baltica Triennale der Fotokunst.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.e-artnow.org/announcement-archive/archive/2008/7/article/ACTION/563/|title=e-artnow.org: Announcement archivek|website=E-artnow.org|accessdate=4 November 2018}}</ref>\n* Vejle Museum of Art, Denmark.\n* Pori Art Museum, Finland.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://kumu.ekm.ee/en/ars-baltica-triennial-of-photographic-art/|title=Ars Baltica. Triennial of Photographic Art \u2014 Kumu Art Museum|website=Kumu.ekm.ee|accessdate=4 November 2018}}</ref>\n* Skopje Paranoia - Freud Museum, London.\n* Museum of Contemporary Art Belgrade, Belgrade.\n* Minority Report - Aarhus Festival of Contemporary Art. Denmark.\n* Neue Galerie Graz - Universalmuseum Joanneum, Graz, Austria.\n* Neue Gesellschaft f\u00fcr Bildende Kunst e.V. (NGBK), Berlin; Stadtgalerie Kiel, Kiel; Andrejsala, Riga; KUMU Art Museum of Estonia, Tallinn.\n\n== Residency== \nBotkyrka konsthall, Stockholm. NIFCA, Helsinki, Nordisk Kunstnarster NDK, Norway, Mamar, Cairo, and HIAP Helsinki.\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Ramadan, Khaled}}\n[[Category:Lebanese artists| Ramadan]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:1965 births]]\n", "text_old": "{{COI|date=September 2018}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2016}}\n\n'''Khaled Ramadan''' (born in 1973) consultant, [[curator]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://maldivespavilion.com/blog/about/|title=About - Maldives Pavilion - 55th Venice Biennale|website=Maldivespavilion.com|accessdate=4 November 2018}}</ref> filmmaker<ref>{{cite web|url=https://vimeo.com/86557708|title=Eye in Hand - E\u015fref Arma\u011fan|website=Vimeo.com|accessdate=4 November 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://vimeo.com/43397737|title=I Told President Mubarak|website=Vimeo.com|accessdate=4 November 2018}}</ref> educator,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.akbild.ac.at/Portal/institute/bildende-kunst/vortrage-events/the-panache-of-artivism-within-the-imperial-cultural-narrative-of-the-middle-east?set_language=de&cl=de&backurl=https://www.akbild.ac.at/resolveuid/44746f5dc4c153575dde87ffed987e0b?b_start=5|title=The Panache of Artivism within the Imperial Cultural Narrative of the Middle East|website=Akbild.ac.at|accessdate=4 November 2018}}</ref> and cultural writer.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.khaledramadan.org/|title=Khaled Ramadan - Don Juan Report|website=Khaledramadan.org|accessdate=4 November 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.artforum.com/diary/id=29765|title=Playing with Fire|website=Artforum.com|accessdate=4 November 2018}}</ref>\nCurrently, he is working as an examiner for the higher artistic educational programmes under The Danish Ministry of Higher Education and Science and as an evaluator of Alto University professorship program. He is the co-editor of the new book, Journalism in Times of War, by Al Jazeera Media Institute, (2018) Aljazeera TV Doha.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://studies.aljazeera.net/en/publications/archive/2016.html|title=2016|website=Studies.aljazeera.net|accessdate=4 November 2018}}</ref> He is the new appointed director of the Media Art Research Space \u2013 MARC, Production and Exhibition Spaces of Art and Film - Antalya, open in April 2017. Previously, Ramadan has worked as director of BMAF, Muscat,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2016/04/27/arts/international/a-helping-hand-for-film-artists-in-oman.html?_r=0|title=A Helping Hand for Film Artists in Oman|website=Nytimes.com|accessdate=4 November 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.selectionsarts.com/2016/03/questions-of-practice/|title=Questions of Practice - Selections Arts|date=30 March 2016|website=Selectionsarts.com|accessdate=4 November 2018}}</ref> a senior advisor for the Maldives Ministry of Culture<ref name=\"maldivespavilion.com\">{{cite web|url=http://www.maldivespavilion.com|title=Maldives Pavilion|website=Maldivespavilion.com|accessdate=4 November 2018}}</ref> and for the Danish Arts Council,<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.kunst.dk/initiativer/kunst-globalisering/interkulturelt-raadgivningsprojekt/the-danish-arts-councils-intercultural-advisory-project/ |title=Archived copy |access-date=9 November 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161109154300/http://www.kunst.dk/initiativer/kunst-globalisering/interkulturelt-raadgivningsprojekt/the-danish-arts-councils-intercultural-advisory-project/ |archive-date=9 November 2016 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all }}</ref> and as an external consultant for the Prince Claus Fund,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.chamberarchive.org/blog/consultants/|title=Consultants - Chamber of Public Secrets|website=Chamberarchive.org|accessdate=4 November 2018}}</ref> the Manifesta Foundation,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://manifesta.org/manifesta-8/|title=Manifesta 8 \u00ab  MANIFESTA|website=Manifesta.org|accessdate=4 November 2018}}</ref> and the Nordic Institute for Contemporary Arts (NIFCA).\n\n==Projects==\nRamadan has curated and co-curated projects like Climate Maters, Ipoh International Art Festival, Malaysia 2019,<ref>https://www.thestar.com.my/lifestyle/culture/2019/11/26/ipoh-international-art-festival-celebrates-the-strength-of-city039s-creative-communities</ref>\u00a0The Third Guangzhou Triennial at the Guangdong Museum of Modern Art, China and UCCA, Beijing; Museo Nacional Centro de Arte Reina Sof\u00eda, Madrid,  KW Berlin, Germany and Outflow, Kumho Museum of Art in Seoul, South Korea. In 2013, he was the appointed curator for the [[Maldives Pavilion]] at the 55th<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.artsy.net/article/maldivespavilion-khaled-ramadans-documentary-maldives-to-be-or|title=Khaled Ramadan\u2019s Documentary: \"Maldives To Be or Not\"|date=25 May 2013|website=Artsy.net|accessdate=4 November 2018}}</ref> [[Venice Biennale]].<ref name=\"maldivespavilion.com\"/> In 2010, together with Chamber of Public Secrets, he was appointed co-curator of [[Manifesta]] 8 in Spain.{{citation needed|date=February 2018}}\n\nRamadan<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.chamberarchive.org|title=Chamber of Public Secrets|website=Chamberarchive.org|accessdate=4 November 2018}}</ref> and Alfredo Cramerotti<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ibraaz.org/platforms/6/responses/11/|title=Response to Platform 6 by CPS Chamber of Public Secrets|website=Ibraaz.org|accessdate=4 November 2018}}</ref> are the co-founder of the art collective Chamber of Public Secrets, which has existed since 2004. In 2006, Ramadan co-founded Doculogia, a platform for critical media.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.doculogia.com|title=DocuLogia|website=Doculogia.com|accessdate=4 November 2018}}</ref> In 2009, Al-Jazeera TV produced a documentary about Ramadan's activities and achievements.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.aljazeera.net/programs/a-date-in-exile/2009/3/29/%D8%AE%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%AF-%D8%B1%D9%85%D8%B6%D8%A7%D9%86 |title=Archived copy |access-date=22 November 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304062337/http://www.aljazeera.net/programs/a-date-in-exile/2009/3/29/%D8%AE%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%AF-%D8%B1%D9%85%D8%B6%D8%A7%D9%86 |archive-date=4 March 2016 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n\nRamadan is a member of the International Association of Art Critics (AICA), and the International Association of Curators of Contemporary Art (IKT) and [21]. He is a nominator of The Sovereign Asian Art Prize, The Jameel Prize, International Award for Contemporary Art and Design, the Prince Claus Fund Awards, and pecial correspondents and nominator for the Future Generation Art Prize, at the Victor Pinchuk Foundation in Kyiv, Ukraine. \n\n==Author==\nHe is the author of Peripheral Insider: Perspectives on Contemporary Internationalism in Visual Culture, published by Copenhagen University Press, 2007.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.co.uk/gp/search?index=books&linkCode=qs&keywords=9788772899671|title=Amazon.co.uk: 9788772899671: Books|website=Amazon.co.uk|accessdate=4 November 2018}}</ref>\nJournalism In Times of War, edited by Awad Joumaa and Khaled Ramadan.<ref>https://www.aljazeera.com/blogs/middleeast/2018/01/journalism-times-war-middle-east-perspective-180124070626008.html</ref>\n\nHe regularly contributes to international magazines<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ebiz.turpin-distribution.com/products/282888-transvisuality-the-cultural-dimension-of-visuality-olume2-visual-organisations.aspx|title=Turpin Distribution. TransVisuality: The Cultural Dimension of Visuality: Volume 2: Visual Organisations|website=Ebiz.turpin-distribution.com|accessdate=4 November 2018}}</ref> and journals<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20050520232043/http://www.mtp.hum.ku.dk/details.asp?ELN=200733]</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.com/Peripheral-Insider-Perspectives-Contemporary-Internationalism/dp/8772899670|title=Peripheral Insider: Perspectives on Contemporary Internationalism in Visual Culture|editor-first=Khaled D.|editor-last=Ramadan|date=12 April 2007|publisher=Museum Tusculanum Press|accessdate=4 November 2018}}</ref> on topics such as art,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.chamberarchive.org/blog/peripheral-insider/|title=Peripheral Insider - Chamber of Public Secrets|website=Chamberarchive.org|accessdate=4 November 2018}}</ref> media, aesthetics and social activism, latest e.g. in Border Thinking: Disassembling Histories of Racialized Violence, ed. Marina Gr\u017eini\u0107, Sternberg Press (2018). Set City, the Age of Reality Cinematography, is the title of Khaled Ramadan\u2019s contribution to the book.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sternberg-press.com/index.php?pageId=1820&l=en&bookId=714|title=Sternberg Press - Marina Gr\u017eini\u0107 (Ed.)|website=Sternberg-press.com|accessdate=4 November 2018}}</ref> Trans-Visuality, published by Liverpool University  Press.\n\n==Works==\nRecent work includes, The Panache of Artivism within the Imperial Narrative of the Middle East, published in 2017 in the book, Independent Republic of Culture - Edited by Serhan Ada, published by Cultural Policy and Management Research Centre, \u0130stanbul Bilgi \u00dcniversitesi Yay\u0131nlar\u0131/ Istanbul Bilgi University Press 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.schermodellarte.org/en/prize-2013/|title=Prize Lo schermo dell'arte Film Festival 2013|website=Schermodellarte.org|accessdate=4 November 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://hivevoices.org/2014/01/06/art-and-its-institutions-in-the-age-of-physical-absentia-by-khaled-ramadan/|title=Khaled Ramadan|date=6 January 2014|website=Hivevoices.org|accessdate=4 November 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.zerobooksonline.com/en/product/independent-republic-of-culture-cultural-policy-and-management-research-centre-kpy-yearbook_29_41056.html?r=22#sthash.9fvBJYwR.dpbs|title=Independent Republic Of Culture Cultural Policy And Management Research Centre (KPY) Yearbook|website=Zero Books Online|accessdate=4 November 2018}}</ref>\n\nRamadan\u2019s art-house filmmaking and theoretical writing has rewarded him a specialisation in cinematic visual analysis and aesthetic framing.\nHe assisted aestheticizing several productions at the Film City in Denmark and the TV station AlJazeera.\n\nHis best cinematic visual analysis contribution is the essay, Set City - Post-Snuff Film and the New Age of Reality Cinematography, in Border Thinking, ed. Prof. Marina Gr\u017eini\u0107, part of the publication series of the Academy of Fine Arts Vienna 2018.\n\n==Writings==\nRamadan\u2019s writing are published with: \nSlavoj Zizek, Irit Rogoff, Benjamin R. Barber, Bernadette Buckley, Horacio Gonz\u00e1lez, Boris Groys, W.J.T. Mitchell, Ken Neil, Lila Pastoriza, James A. Walker, Peter Weibel, Joseba Zulaika, Hamid Dabashi, Thomas McEvilley, Sarat Maharaj, Rasheed Araeen, Gavin Jantjes, Simon Sheikh, Maaretta Jaukkuri, Gao Shiming, Max Ryyn\u00e4nen, Zygmunt Bauman and Antonio Zaya.\n\n==Videography==\nThe Return of the Real, with artist Veronica Bape, Dale Norway 2019. Red Line, with artist Kari Steihaug, Norway 2019. RobOman. Arabian Gulf, 2018; Outsourcing Torture. AJ co-production.  2016; Floating Community. Cambodia 2016; Romiah Selfie. Lebanon, 2015; Caf\u00e9 Fishawy. Egypt, 2014; Maldives To Be or Not. Maldives 2013; The Shadow of San Anton. Spain, 2010. I Told President Mubarak. Egypt 2010.  Eyes in Hand, about blind artist Esraf Armagan. Spain 2010. Out of Gaza. Gaza strip, 2009. Quest for the Brotherhood. Egypt, 2008.\nArab Media Landscape. Dubai, UAE, 2007;  Mapping the South. Lebanon, 2006;  Comrade Alfredo Neri. Denmark-Sweden-Italy, 2005;  Wide Power. Lebanon, 2004.\n\n==Participation==\n*Climate Maters, Ipoh International Art Festival, Malaysia 2019<ref>http://portipoh.com.my/phone/screening-and-talk.html</ref>\n*\u201cFrom a Place of Darkness\u201d Contemporary Istanbul, curated by Gulsen Bal 2019 <ref>https://www.contemporaryistanbul.com</ref>\n*For the Love of Air Liquid. Curated by Alfredo Cramerotti and Khaled Ramadan, Opening exhibition - Media Art Research Center (MARC), Antalya, April 2018. http://www.chamberarchive.org/blog/for-the-love-of-air-liquid/\n*What is left? Frei_raum Q21 exhibition space, Vienna, Austria, 2016.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.q21.at/en/program/c/programmdetail/what-is-left-1/|title=Q21|website=MuseumsQuartier Wien|accessdate=4 November 2018}}</ref>\n*Be-diversity, MUSE di Trento, Italy 2015.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.muse.it/it/Esplora/mostre-temporanee/Archivio/Pagine/Be-diversity.aspx|title=Be-diversity|website=Muse.it|accessdate=4 November 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=vtCpzg2dHgA|title=Be-diversity: Platform: RTTR: Aboulkheir Breigheche|author=Stefano Cagol|date=22 August 2015|accessdate=4 November 2018|publisher=[[YouTube]]}}</ref>\n*A Room of His Own, The Artsonje Center Seoul 2014.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://koreajoongangdaily.joins.com/news/article/article.aspx?aid=2999452|title=Exhibit explores changing position of men|website=Korea JoongAng Daily|accessdate=4 November 2018